 16  /-- We define an equivalence as a (half)-adjoint equivalence, a pair of functors with
 17    a unit and counit which are natural isomorphisms and the triangle law `Fη ≫ εF = 1`, or in other
 18    words the composite `F ⟶ FGF ⟶ F` is the identity.
 19  
 20    The triangle equation is written as a family of equalities between morphisms, it is more
 21    complicated if we write it as an equality of natural transformations, because then we would have
 22    to insert natural transformations like `F ⟶ F1`.
 23  -/
